# Rasm C# Specs

Read `.claude/skills/cs-testing/SKILL.md`, `tests/csharp/AGENTS.md`, nearest test `AGENTS.md`, and relevant `docs/testing-libs/<tool>/api.md`.

## Ownership

- Mirror source ownership: one spec file targets one source file or tight concern.
- Keep local generators in the spec until at least two specs need the shape.
- Promote to `_testkit` only for higher-order law, oracle, generator, or serializer capability.

## Oracles

- Prefer closed form, smaller model, fixture geometry, metamorphic relation, or independent `Numeric` oracle.
- Reject implementation mirrors, current-output snapshots, shape-only primary assertions, and stub-receipt construction.
- Use distinct-value product generators so swaps and ignored fields fail.
- Investigate product code first before weakening a failing law.

## Density

- Prefer one generated law over several facts when one sample can attack construction, projection, unsupported output, failure category, receipt metadata, and an independent oracle.
- Use `Spec.ForAll`, `Spec.Cases`, `Spec.Metamorphic`, `Spec.SmartEnumKeysUnique`, `Gens`, and `Numeric`.
- Use `Gen.Where(...).Select(...)` or lifted `Fin` filtering; never `Select+throw`.
- Convert SmartEnum/Union case sweeps to `[Theory]` or `MemberData` when Stryker needs separately killable targets.

## Validation

Run `bash scripts/test.sh` for managed specs. Use `TEST_TARGET=<csproj> bash scripts/test.sh` for non-default test projects.
